Rating: 4
I *loved* this recipe. I used vermouth rather than wine because it's what I had on hand, plus added about a 1/4 lb of crumbled blue cheese at the very end of the cooking time for the sauce. It thickened it nicely and gave it an extra kick. I used the veal and mushroom sauce to top angel hair pasta and broccoli rabe sauteed in olive oil and garlic. Even my daughter enjoyed it, and she is not a meat eater. Next time, I will add shallots and double the mushrooms and sauce if I serve it with pasta. There were NO leftovers!

